tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: All measured parameters are within or very close to normal ranges, except for a minimally elevated chloride, which is likely not clinically significant in isolation. Renal function, glucose metabolism, and electrolyte balance appear stable. No acute laboratory abnormalities detected; recommend clinical correlation and routine monitoring.
